      "type": "heading",
      "value": "What is Teleport?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Teleport is a built-in Vue feature that allows you to render a component's content in a different part of the DOM."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Why Use Teleport?"
    },
    {
      "type": "list",
      "value": [
        "**Render modals outside root**",
        "**Avoid CSS overflow issues**",
        "**Improve layout flexibility**",
        "**Control DOM structure easily**"
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Basic Syntax"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<teleport to=\"#modal\">\n  <div class=\"modal\">Hello Modal</div>\n</teleport>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Target Element"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<div id=\"modal\"></div>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Conditional Teleport"
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<teleport to=\"#modal\" v-if=\"show\">\n  <div>Popup</div>\n</teleport>"
    },
